verbose_text: Taken together, these data demonstrate that treatment of monocytes and osteoclast precursors with BiP reduces M-CSF- and RANKL induced signal transduction and activation of the essential osteoclastogenic transcription factors NF-kappaB, c-Fos, and NFATc1, thereby providing insights into the mechanisms whereby BiP could inhibit osteoclast differentiation and resorptive activity in vivo.
